  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).
  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).
  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. supervisions.notes: The Court ordered restitution in the stipulated amount of $61,156.07 payable to Wisconsin Support Collections Trust Fund - to be paid first.

Pay all supervision fees.
Provide a DNA sample if not previously done so - pay surcharge.
Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs after restitution is paid in full.
The Court ordered that all financial obligations and restitution be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision. Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.

superMiscConds.notes: Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions: Firearm possession and Voting.
No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause.

Obtain mental health assessment if necessary complete follow-up treatment - take all prescription medication as prescribed by a treating physician.
Participate in Cognitive Thinking program.
Participate in Parenting class.
Participate in Anger Management class if deemed appropriate.
Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the of probation agent.
Obtain AODA assessment and if necessary successfully complete follow-up treatment.

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.
